The paper deals with topics related to domain theory, topology, and set theory, which are typically covered in the sub-categories of Logic (cs.LO, cs.LOgic), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), and Programming Languages (cs.PL). The focus on fixed-point equations and coalgebras also suggests a connection to the Theory of Computation (cs.TC) sub-category, but this is less likely given the emphasis on topology and set theory.
